    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span>After getting an anonymous phone call, Inspector Sartaj Singh is trying to find clues to track the location of caller. He got the information from a RAW agent that in order to track the location, he needs to gather following information.\n\nIn Mumbai city there are **N** locations and **N-1** roads connecting them (there is a path between every pair of locations). Each location has a particular **TYPE** associated with it (not necessaily unique and represented by a lowercase alphabet) **TYPE<sub>i</sub>**. RAW has provided Sartaj a pattern **P**, continuous occurence of which is an anomaly. Sartaj needs to find the total number of such anomalies.\n\nWe say there is occurence of pattern **P** if for path        \n<center>**v<sub>1</sub> v<sub>2</sub> ... v<sub>k</sub>**</center>  \nWe have,    \n <center> **k = length(P)** </center>    \nand  \n<center>**type<sub>v<sub>i</sub></sub> = P<sub>i</sub> \u2200 1 \u2264 i \u2264 length(P)**\n</center>\n\n<strong>NOTE: </strong>Two occurences of anomalies are **different** if either atleast one of the **locations in path** is different or **ordering of locations** is different.\n\n\n###Input:\n\n-First line contains the number of locations **N**.  \n-Second line contains a string of length **N** containing only lowercase alphabets, <em>ith</em> character of which represent type of <em>ith</em> location.  \n-Third line contains a string **P**, representing the pattern.  \n-Next **N-1** lines contains two integers **U** and **V**,  representing there is bidirectional road between location **U** and **V**.\n\n###Output:\nSingle integer containing the total number of anomalies.\n\n###Constraints \n1 \u2264 N \u2264 10<sup>5</sup>\n\n1 \u2264 length(P) \u2264 3*10<sup>3</sup>\n\n###Sample Input: \n8  \nababaaca   \nabab   \n1 2   \n1 4    \n1 7      \n2 3  \n4 5  \n4 6   \n7 8  \n\n![image](https://codechef_shared.s3.amazonaws.com/download/HYC/External_contest_images/INQU2018/ANOMALY.png)\n\n###Sample Output:  \n3    \n\t\n###EXPLANATION:  \nPaths:    \n3-2-1-4    \n5-4-1-2    \n6-4-1-2    \n",
